    - The Three Armies Bureau (Samgunjbu) was a military institution established early in the Chosŏn dynasty to identify and develop talent through both literary and martial education.
    - The 'Six Virtues, Six Practices, and Six Arts' refer to the Zhou dynasty's comprehensive system of moral and practical education described in classical texts like the Rites of Zhou.
    - Jeong Do-jeon (鄭道傳, 1342-1398) was a prominent statesman and scholar who served as chief architect of Chosŏn's founding institutions under King Taejo.
    - The 'presented scholars' (jinsa) reference an ancient examination system where candidates progressed through increasingly rigorous evaluation before receiving official appointment.
